snippet.textDisplay:
Honestly I have trouble telling if this is a daemonic/psychic entity, or something more like a C'tan Shard. The sphere itself seems to be living metal as opposed to flesh, and the sphere pulses with a blueish light, when I normally associated shades of red with psychic/daemonic powers. The desert world itself makes me think more of a Necron tombworld than a daemonworld.


Don't get me wrong, the project is absolutely fantastic and I loved it, I just want some clarification on what exactly the sphere was.

EDIT: NOPE, I'M WRONG
I THINK I FOUND ONE. In the entirety of this masterpiece, I think I've finally found an animation error - 7:12 he fires 3 shots with the bolter in view, but the third shot (and last one before he yeets himself) doesn't have the bolt carrier move to open the ejection port for the expended cartridge to cycle out, whereas the previous shots do. To find an error in this seems like an attempt to redefine "needle in a haystack".


also, yes, because the last shot is a different sound it could be the indication of an empty magazine, thus he jumped for cover to reload, and the empty cartridge is still in the chamber which will be cycled out within the reload. BUT LET ME HAVE THIS.
